FBIS4-37541 "drnes120_k_94009" FBIS-NES-94-120 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 IRAQ Saddam Orders Increase in Benefits for Retirees Saddam Orders Increase in Benefits for Retirees JN2006114294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1030 GMT 20 Jun 94 JN2006114294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God watch over him, has ordered an additional cost of living allowance for retirees who had served for 25 years or more and whose salaries and allocations now are less than 500 dinars. The additional allowance amounts to 25 percent of the retiree's monthly salary and allocations and is effective as of 1 February 1994. This came in a notice by the Presidential Office to the Finance Ministry and other competent parties.
